Package: token2-fido-bridge
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, pcscd, libpcsclite1
Recommends: pcsc-tools
Description: use smartcards as FIDO2/WebAuthn keys (PC/SC to USB-HID bridge)
 token2-fido-bridge lets browsers use PC/SC smartcards (contact or NFC) as
 FIDO2/WebAuthn security keys on Linux. It creates a virtual USB-HID FIDO2
 authenticator via the Linux uhid interface and relays CTAP2/U2F traffic to
 the card over PC/SC.
 .
 A lightweight native C++ daemon: a single binary of a few hundred kilobytes
 with no interpreter or runtime dependencies beyond the system PC/SC library.
 Works with Chromium/Chrome and, via a bundled udev rule, Snap-confined
 Firefox.
 .
 Maintained by Token2 (https://www.token2.com).
